### Event Information: Tamper Evident Challenge

**Title:** CON - Tamper Evident Challenge

**Event Description:**
The F.I.B (Federal Investigation Bureau) Tamper Challenge invites participants to help break into a package to alter some evidence. The challenge consists of two sections: Beginner and Advanced, allowing participants to compete in both with a maximum of two members per team. The goal is to reach the center of the package and retrieve and alter the data without leaving a trace.

**Challenge Details:**
- **Start Date:** Tuesday, October 22, 2023, at 1:00 PM MDT
- **End Date:** Thursday, October 24, 2023, at 4:30 PM MDT
- Participants will have access to an array of tamper-evident devices within the packages.
- **Game Objective:** Get to the center of the package without detection and return all materials, regardless of success.

**How to Participate:**
- Sign up at the Tamper Evident Community booth.
- Research different types of tamper-evident devices and prepare tools like syringes, hair dryers, and other items for the challenge.
- Participants will receive a mini badge for joining the contest.

**Judging Criteria:**
- Participants are evaluated on their ability to access the package without leaving evidence (physical marks, swapped ID numbers, incorrect assembly).
- In the case of a tie, speed will be the determining factor.

**Key Rules:**
1. Get in undetected and leave no trace.
2. Teamwork and collaboration are encouraged, but teams must have only two members.
3. Return all materials, even if unsuccessful.

**Hours of Operation:**
- **Contest Start:** Tuesday – Noon
- **Contest End:** Thursday – 4:30 PM
- **Winners Announced:** During the closing ceremony on Friday.

**Booth Hours:**
- Tuesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- Wednesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- Friday: 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM

**Note:** This challenge promotes skill development in tampering techniques while ensuring ethical standards are maintained in a competitive setting.